{
    "biomes":  [
                   {
                       "characterName":  "Gandalf",
                       "banner":  "banner_gandalf_mithrandir",
                       "artifacts":  [

                                     ],
                       "description":  "\u003cu\u003eGandalf\u003c/u\u003e is the grey pilgrim, a wanderer of hidden roads and quiet counsel. He walks the edge between shadow and hope, guiding the small and the humble because he knows their courage can outlast any sword. He trusts in patience, in wisdom earned by travel, and in the spark that lights when others have given in to fear.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHis road stretches beyond the Shire into the wider lanes of Eriador and the scattered strongholds of the Free Peoples. He gathers trusted companions, listens for uneasy rumors, and searches old ground for relics and allies that still matter long after the first road is taken.",
                       "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e Grey and uncommitted — \u003csprite name=\"commander\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"agent\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"emmissary\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e spread thin, armies light. No road yet chosen.",
                       "variants":  [
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "gandalf",
                                            "displayName":  "Mithrandir",
                                            "description":  "\u003cu\u003eMithrandir\u003c/u\u003e, pilgrim of the West, passes like an old song through Rivendell, Lothlorien, and the hidden paths where the Wise still keep watch against the ancient Shadow. In him abide memory, mercy, and the secret fire set against a darkness older than the kingdoms of Men, and where he treads, veils are lifted and the designs of the Enemy are read before they ripen to ruin.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eUnder \u003cb\u003eMithrandir\u003c/b\u003e, the game turns toward revelation, warding, foresight, and spellcraft wielded with patient precision rather than open might.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e The grey wanderer walks every road — \u003csprite name=\"commander\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"agent\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"emmissary\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e all grown deep, and his host many-armed: Elves, scouts, and fleets. \u003csprite name=\"gold\"\u003e runs swift; the price of every open road is steep.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "gandalf",
                                            "banner":  "banner_gandalf_mithrandir",
                                            "characterName":  "Mithrandir"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "stormcrow",
                                            "displayName":  "Stormcrow",
                                            "description":  "\u003cu\u003eStormcrow\u003c/u\u003e they name him in the troubled halls of kings, for his coming is the whisper before the war-horn, the black wing against a paling sky. He is seen where Rohan wavers, where Gondor keeps weary watch, and where the old roads of the North begin once more to feel the breath of Angmar, Isengard, and Mordor upon their stones.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant carries the weight of vigilance, strained loyalties, bitter choices, and endurance beneath a darkening sky.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e The Stormcrow\u0027s web of lands \u003csprite name=\"pc\"\u003e and roads produces \u003csprite name=\"mounts\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"leather\"\u003e in abundance — needing no supply line. His armies are thin and sorcery \u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e slight; he wins by presence, not force.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "stormcrow",
                                            "banner":  "banner_gandalf_stormcrow",
                                            "characterName":  "Stormcrow"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "disturber_of_the_peace",
                                            "displayName":  "Disturber of Peace",
                                            "description":  "At Bag End and along the Bree-road, in fireworks, whispers, and the sudden knock at dusk, \u003cu\u003ethe Disturber of the Peace\u003c/u\u003e unsettles the comfortable world. From those small provocations spring journeys, riddles, unlikely fellowships, and the turning of humble lives toward deeds that will outlast towers and crowns.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant leans into the Shire, Bree-land, and the long road through Eriador: hobbit-scale mischief, roadside wonders, strange meetings, and the little interruptions that reroute an entire tale.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e A mischief deck: \u003csprite name=\"agent\"\u003e saturates every shadow, archers \u003csprite name=\"bow\"\u003e ready where blades would be heard. Hobbits and wanderers turn Bree-land into disruption. No sorcery \u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e, no heavy arms — only the deed done before it is suspected.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "disturber_of_the_peace",
                                            "banner":  "banner_gandalf_disturber_of_the_peace",
                                            "characterName":  "Disturber of the Peace"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "tharkun",
                                            "displayName":  "Tharkun",
                                            "description":  "\u003cu\u003eTharkun\u003c/u\u003e is the name the Dwarves remember: friend of the House of Durin, walker in the deeps, and counselor in halls where stone keeps faith longer than flesh. He knows the grief buried in Khazad-dum, the splendor of Erebor restored, and the peril that lies ever beside gold, mithril, and the pride of mountain kings.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant turns toward hidden wealth, mountain fortitude, and alliances tempered in the dark under stone.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e Gandalf as dwarf-friend: \u003csprite name=\"commander\"\u003e towers high, \u003csprite name=\"mithril\"\u003e flows self-sustaining from deep veins, Dwarven axemen grinding hard endurance under stone. No sorcery \u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e — what he builds, he builds with toil.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "tharkun",
                                            "banner":  "banner_gandalf_tharkun",
                                            "characterName":  "Tharkun"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "gandalf_the_white",
                                            "displayName":  "The White",
                                            "description":  "Clothed in white and returned from death, \u003cu\u003ethe White Rider\u003c/u\u003e comes from Fangorn like a judgment upon despair. He breaks the pride of Saruman, scatters the poison of Wormtongue, and stands in the last defence of the West as hidden wisdom is transfigured into open command beneath the sunlit banners of hope.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant is one of cleansing, renewal, fearless command, and the sudden turning of darkness beneath a greater light.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e Returned white authority: \u003csprite name=\"commander\"\u003e dominant, heavy horse and fleets of Gondor and Rohan at his back, lords rallied wide \u003csprite name=\"pc\"\u003e. The mage\u0027s art \u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e is spent — he leads now by command, not craft.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "gandalf_the_white",
                                            "banner":  "banner_gandalf_gandalf_the_white",
                                            "characterName":  "Gandalf the White"
                                        }
                                    ],
