                   {
                       "characterName":  "Saruman",
                       "artifacts":  [

                                     ],
                       "description":  "\u003cu\u003eSaruman\u003c/u\u003e is the master of Orthanc, once the chief of the wise, now the architect of his own dominion.His voice bends courts, his mind measures every weakness, and his ambition refuses to wait for permission. He builds in silence, gathering strength behind fair words, and he intends to remake the world in the image of his will.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHis design begins with a careful reach into the courts of Rohan, the securing of a pliant voice, and the quiet unearthing of power long buried. From Orthanc he turns influence into force and raises the first ranks of his war.",
                       "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e The white before the breaking — \u003csprite name=\"commander\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"agent\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"emmissary\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e each open, \u003csprite name=\"steel\"\u003e already turning. No road yet chosen.",
                       "banner":  "banner_saruman_saruman_the_white",
                       "variants":  [
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "saruman_the_white",
                                            "displayName":  "The White",
                                            "description":  "\u003cu\u003eSaruman the White\u003c/u\u003e stands in the majesty of Orthanc, chief of the Istari, master of lore, ring-craft, and the long devices of the Wise. His voice is a weapon finer than steel, entering the counsels of kings and bending proud hearts with honeyed reason until obedience seems wisdom and surrender seems peace.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant favors influence, manipulation, and command exercised with polished restraint.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e Voice, art, and argument — \u003csprite name=\"agent\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"emmissary\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e all keen, with events reshaping the board. His host is numerous but common-born \u003csprite name=\"leather\"\u003e, and his territories \u003csprite name=\"pc\"\u003e spread thin.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "saruman_the_white",
                                            "banner":  "banner_saruman_saruman_the_white",
                                            "characterName":  "Saruman the White"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "of_many_colours",
                                            "displayName":  "Saruman Multicoloured",
                                            "description":  "Saruman \u003cu\u003ethe Many-Coloured\u003c/u\u003e shatters the white that once signified order and reveals the glittering fracture of pride. In that figure are gathered ring-lore, engines, subtle arts, and the cold brilliance of a mind that would rival the makers of old, yet all are bent now toward dominion, display, and the blasphemous imitation of a power once sent to oppose the Shadow.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant leans into grand sorcery, layered effects, and the dangerous splendor of power unbound by humility.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e The widest host and richest harvest — cavalry \u003csprite name=\"mounts\"\u003e no other master fields so deep, \u003csprite name=\"leather\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"gold\"\u003e in flood, grand sorcery \u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e and many colours. \u003csprite name=\"iron\"\u003e is scarce; the forge runs cold.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "of_many_colours",
                                            "banner":  "banner_saruman_of_many_colours",
                                            "characterName":  "Saruman Multicoloured"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "the_white_hand",
                                            "displayName":  "The White Hand",
                                            "description":  "\u003cu\u003eThe White Hand\u003c/u\u003e rises over Isengard like a blasphemous banner, and beneath it the world is remade in smoke, iron, and ruin. Fangorn falls to the axe, the furnaces thunder without ceasing, and from the black pits march Uruk-hai and wolf-riders, forged for the breaking of Helm\u0027s Deep and the humiliation of the Mark.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant drives forward with industry, relentless pressure, and the hard discipline of Isengard at war.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e Isengard\u0027s forged war machine: \u003csprite name=\"commander\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"agent\"\u003e drive iron-will infantry, furnaces thunder, Uruk discipline makes aggression systematic. No sorcery \u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e; what he lacks in art, he pays in \u003csprite name=\"leather\"\u003e.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "the_white_hand",
                                            "banner":  "banner_saruman_the_white_hand",
                                            "characterName":  "The White Hand"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "sharkey",
                                            "displayName":  "Sharkey",
                                            "description":  "\u003cu\u003eSharkey\u003c/u\u003e is the name they give him in the Shire, and he wears it like a snarl. Stripped of tower and art and title, what remains is spite: a bitter will that turns the Shire\u0027s fields into quarries, pens the hobbits in lockholes, and burns what it cannot own. He does not conquer — he poisons. He does not command armies — he directs ruffians, extortion, and the slow erasure of everything pleasant about a people who never harmed him.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant operates without sorcery and without great armies. It wins through intimidation, pipe-weed monopoly, occupation of settlements, and the grinding cruelty of petty authority over a land that has no walls.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e No towers, no spells \u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e, no cavalry \u003csprite name=\"mounts\"\u003e — Sharkey rules through \u003csprite name=\"agent\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"emmissary\"\u003e and the fear they carry. \u003csprite name=\"gold\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"leather\"\u003e flow from an occupied Shire; his ruffians are cheap and mean.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "sharkey",
                                            "banner":  "banner_saruman_sharkey",
                                            "characterName":  "Sharkey"
                                        }
                                    ],
