                   {
                       "characterName":  "Sauron",
                       "artifacts":  [

                                     ],
                       "description":  "\u003cu\u003eSauron\u003c/u\u003e is the Dark Lord returned, a will of iron that has never forgotten its claim. From Barad-dur he bends the lands through fear and patience, drawing all things toward a single purpose. He does not need love or loyalty, only obedience, and he will take it by force or by dread.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe hunt begins in the shadow of Minas Morgul, where the trail is secured and a relic of power is drawn from cursed ground. From there the march moves toward the Black Gate, where the first disciplined hosts take shape under a hard command.",
                       "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e Every shadow he has ever worn still breathes — \u003csprite name=\"commander\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"agent\"\u003e\u003csprite name=\"emmissary\"\u003e waking, cavalry \u003csprite name=\"mounts\"\u003e restless. No shape yet fixed.",
                       "banner":  "banner_sauron_the_dark_eye",
                       "variants":  [
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "the_dark_eye",
                                            "displayName":  "The Dark Eye",
                                            "description":  "\u003cu\u003eThe Dark Eye\u003c/u\u003e burns above Barad-dur like a star of malice that never sets, sleepless over Gorgoroth, the Black Gate, and the dead roads beneath Ephel Duath. It is dread made watchful, a will that peers through palantiri, dreams, and trembling rumor until no secrecy feels safe and every hidden movement seems already betrayed.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant is built on exposure, fear, and a suffocating dominion that narrows the enemy\u0027s every choice.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e Nothing hidden survives — \u003csprite name=\"commander\"\u003e towers above all peers, captains answer as one across twenty domains \u003csprite name=\"pc\"\u003e. Heavy infantry holds every field; he is slow to mount \u003csprite name=\"mounts\"\u003e.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "the_dark_eye",
                                            "banner":  "banner_sauron_the_dark_eye",
                                            "characterName":  "Sauron"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "the_deceiver",
                                            "displayName":  "The Deceiver",
                                            "description":  "\u003cu\u003eThe Deceiver\u003c/u\u003e walks in the memory of the Second Age: Annatar, Lord of Gifts, whispering to the smiths of Eregion; corrupter of Celebrimbor\u0027s great labor; and dark counselor to the pride of Numenor in its final blasphemy. Fair-seeming, patient, and terrible in wisdom misused, he raises no banner at first, but teaches the mighty to forge their own chains until kingdoms drown, temples burn, and the bent world itself bears witness to his fraud.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant leans into deceit, seduction, false gifts, and the hidden mastery won long before the sword is drawn.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e The Deceiver\u0027s tongue \u003csprite name=\"emmissary\"\u003e outpaces every sword; \u003csprite name=\"gold\"\u003e and armies flood from his dominion, PCs \u003csprite name=\"pc\"\u003e spanning wide. Little sorcery \u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e and few great events — his power is bought, not conjured.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "the_deceiver",
                                            "banner":  "banner_sauron_the_deceiver",
                                            "characterName":  "Annatar"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "the_necromancer",
                                            "displayName":  "The Necromancer",
                                            "description":  "\u003cu\u003eThe Necromancer\u003c/u\u003e broods in Dol Guldur, and Greenwood the Great withers into Mirkwood beneath the shadow of his hidden throne. From that hill of sorcery crawl spiders, wraiths, and corrupted things, while fear seeps through root and branch until the very forest seems to remember some older terror returning from forgotten ages.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant favors haunted pressure, monstrous servants, dark sorcery, and corruption that lingers long after the first blow.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e From Dol Guldur, \u003csprite name=\"mithril\"\u003e seeps endlessly; dark art \u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e and heavy infantry grind the forest to shadow. No agents \u003csprite name=\"agent\"\u003e and no emissaries \u003csprite name=\"emmissary\"\u003e — he does not parley; he waits.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "the_necromancer",
                                            "banner":  "banner_sauron_the_necromancer",
                                            "characterName":  "The Necromancer"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "shadow_of_the_east",
                                            "displayName":  "Shadow of the East",
                                            "description":  "\u003cu\u003eThe Shadow of the East\u003c/u\u003e stirs where the sun rises over the Sea of Rhûn and the red war-spears of the Easterlings gather beneath whispers older than their tribal kings. Sauron has walked there in secret, leaving gifts of iron and fear among the horse-lords and wagon-folk, and now the eastern steppes breed armies that look westward with hungry patience. From the lands beyond the maps of the Wise, a tide of bondage and blade gathers, and the Free Peoples feel the first cold wind of a storm born far beyond their walls.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant is built on eastern hordes, dark diplomacy, and the patient raising of vast armies through emissary craft and whispered threats.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e The shadow rides east on tireless horse \u003csprite name=\"mounts\"\u003e — cavalry and agents \u003csprite name=\"agent\"\u003e spreading darkness before armies know it has arrived. No spells \u003csprite name=\"mage\"\u003e and no envoys \u003csprite name=\"emmissary\"\u003e; he moves too fast for councils.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "shadow_of_the_east",
                                            "banner":  "banner_shadow_of_the_east",
                                            "characterName":  "Shadow of the East"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "variantId":  "the_iron_crown",
                                            "displayName":  "The Iron Crown",
                                            "description":  "\u003cu\u003eThe Iron Crown\u003c/u\u003e rises in the Witch-realm of Angmar, where the Witch-king wears cold dominion over the ruined hills of Eriador. He does not come with open war at first, but with deception, plague, and the slow breaking of hope among the Men of Arnor and Cardolan. From the mountain holds of the North, Orcs and Trolls are bred like a pestilence, while slavers and false counsel gnaw at the edges of a kingdom that no longer trusts its own shadow. Dark sorcery flows from Carn Dûm like a black river, and the crown upon the Witch-king\u0027s brow is the seal of a winter that will not end until the last hearth in the West is cold.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis variant favors deceit, recruitment through terror, slaving, monstrous hordes from the mountains, and sorcery that bends the will before the blade is drawn.",
                                            "deckIdentity":  "\u003csprite name=\"deck\"\u003e \u003ci\u003eDeck identity:\u003c/i\u003e The Iron Crown forges strength in iron \u003csprite name=\"iron\"\u003e and commands columns that do not break \u003csprite name=\"fortified\"\u003e. No spy \u003csprite name=\"agent\"\u003e and few diplomats \u003csprite name=\"emmissary\"\u003e; it does not negotiate — it occupies.",
                                            "subdeckId":  "the_iron_crown",
                                            "banner":  "banner_the_iron_crown",
                                            "characterName":  "The Iron Crown"
                                        }
                                    ],
